title: For Sale:  275 Gallon Polypropylene Tank
postcontent:
I have a few 275 Gallon Polypropylene tanks. These tanks have a dimension of 40"x48"x52"(tall) and are a cubed shape. These tanks are once used and are being recycled. The product previously was water based and very easy to clean out. The tanks have a galvanized steel cage around the tank and has a HD plastic or metal pallet/skid that it sits on (sometimes the pallets are wood but rarely). 

These tanks weigh approximately 130 pounds empty. The tanks of a 6"/12" fill cap located on the top of the tank and a 2" ball valve at the base of the tank. These tanks are solid and will not leak. 
There is an infinite usage list for these tanks; storing water for livestock, storing water for a garden or orchard, catching rain, using for a reservoir for a cabin or outhouse, to use for aquaculture or aquaponics, a one person hillbilly hot tub, use to transport liquids, store liquids (just make sure that they won't eat through polypropylene), store waste oil, store de-icer, etc... The sky is the limit. 

You can start a seal coating company or use it to move water around for a power washing company. I have people making bio diesel and black diesel in these tanks as well. 

1 Tank for $60 and 2 tanks for $100. 

If you have any questions or concerns feel free to email me or call me at REDACTED ask for Andrew. I can deliver for a reasonable fee.  

Notes: You can easily put two of them in a full pick up and three of them in a full pick up if you put the tail gate down. You can put one tank in a 6' bed and two tanks in a 6' bed if you put the tail gate down. 

The photo is tanks from a previous shipment though my current tanks are very similar if not the same. 

I am interested in bartering for items as well; silver, gold, ammunition, firearms, tools, welding gear, guys things, motorcycle related things, aquaponic and aquaculture related items (fish fingerlings, etc. . .), hunting gear, military/police gear, HAM radio equipment, SCUBA gear, etc. . . The worse thing I could say is no, that I am not interested in the trade.

Colt Model 1855 Sidehammer Pocket Revolver. This is second variation. Fine collectible condition on this rare Civil War era revolver. The Colt Model 1855 Sidehammer, also known as the Colt Root Revolver after engineer Elisha K. Root (1808-1865), was a cap & ball single action pocket revolver used during the American Civil War and made by the Colt's Patent Fire Arms Manufacturing Company in two calibers: .28 and .31. In the revolver configuration of the patented revolving mechanism, only one model of revolver was produced. The two only available calibers for the revolver were .28 and .31. title: For Sale/Trade:  Cigar Store Indian--6Ft--Gallagher
postcontent:
Glock-Ruger-Colt-Smith&Wesson-Remington-Beretta-Sig-Kimber-Walther-Etc

Frank Gallaghers ancestor, one of the first wooden Indian carvers, started carving his Indians in the 1840's. His great, great grandson Frank is known to be one of approximately 12 true full-blooded Man-Dan Indians still living. Unfortunately, the Man-Dan village was infected by small pox which practically wiped out the entire tribe. Frank's ancestor however, was away from the village at the time, working for a furniture maker. The furniture maker's name was Samuel Gallagher. Following the custom of Indian laborers of that era, Frank took his employer's last name as his own. One of the original Wooden Indians are on display in the Smithsonian Institute. The Gallaghers continue the art of carving as their ancestor would want it; the old way - the right way - by hand.
You've seen them at Trading Post, you've seen them at souvenir shops, now you have the opportunity to own your own Cigar Store Wooden Indian. Carved by the same family that carved the very first one for a man that owned Gallaghers Furniture Store, back in the 1800's. A truly unique conversation piece, for home, office or store front. Own a piece of American heritage, a Frank Gallagher original sculpture.

 The .22 caliber HK 416 is loaded with authentic features. From its appearance, feel, and operation, right down to the sling swivel incorporated into the stock, the 416 D145RS is a replica in every sense.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Kel Tec PLR22 Semi auto tactical pistol

postcontent:
The PLR-22 pistol is chambered for the popular and economical .22 Long Rifle cartridge (.22LR). It is based on the 5.56mm NATO chambered PLR-16 pistol and shares many parts including the grip and front and rear sights. The PLR-22 is not a simple conversion kit, it is a standalone firearm chambered for the .22LR and is designed for target shooting, plinking, or small game hunting. The PLR-22 and SU-22 operate by blowback action and have a 4140 steel bolt that rides on steel guide rails inside the polymer receiver. The ejector is attached to one of the guide rails and the recoil spring is located above the barrel. The cross-bolt safety and magazine release operate identically to the PLR-16 and SU-16.

TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS

Calibers: .22LR
Weight unloaded: 2.8lbs 1.3kg
Length: 18.5" 469.9mm
Barrel length: 10.1" 256.5mm
Sight radius: 12.5" 317.5mm
Twist: 1:16"
Capacity: 26 rounds, Atchison compatible
Trigger pull: 5.5-7.5 lbs 24.4-33.4N
The PLR-22 and SU-22 will accept many of the same accessories as the PLR-16 and SU-16 including the slings, stocks, and compact forend. The rear sight is adjustable for windage and the front sight is adjustable for elevation. An integrated picatinny rail on top will accept a multitude of sighting options. The muzzle end of the barrel is threaded ½"-28 to accept standard attachments such as a muzzle brake. A 26 round semi-transparent magazine is included and it will accept magazines designed for the Atchison M-16 conversion.
